Nat20 — Pure-Python D&D 5e SRD 5.2 rules engine + dataset.

This repository is a uv workspace of two packages with distinct licenses:

  - dnd5e-engine  — the rules engine CODE, licensed under the MIT License
                    (see packages/dnd5e-engine/LICENSE). It ships NO SRD data;
                    the canonical rules content lives in dnd5e-srd-data, which
                    the engine consumes at runtime via BundledAssetLoader.

  - dnd5e-srd-data — the bundled D&D 5e SRD dataset, distributed under the
                    Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License
                    (CC-BY-4.0). https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/
                    (see packages/dnd5e-srd-data/LICENSE).

The rules this project implements derive from the D&D 5e System Reference
Document. The provenance of that ruleset (carried by the dnd5e-srd-data
dataset, distributed under CC-BY-4.0) is:

Attribution:
- Portions derived from the Foundry VTT dnd5e system
  (https://github.com/foundryvtt/dnd5e), CC-BY-4.0.
- Cross-checked against open5e (https://open5e.com), CC-BY-4.0, and the
  5e-bits/5e-database project (https://github.com/5e-bits/5e-database), MIT.
- Original source: System Reference Document 5.1 and 5.2 by Wizards of the
  Coast LLC, CC-BY-4.0.

See each package's NOTICE and LICENSE for the license texts. The pinned upstream
sources are recorded in packages/dnd5e-srd-data/raw_sources/PINS.json and
raw_sources/README.md; the raw upstream snapshots themselves are regenerated locally
(via `make refresh-upstream`), not distributed in this repository.

